snippet: The fire at a mosque near Ramallah last month was most likely caused by an electrical fault, the police said.
abstract: Israeli police conclude that November fire at West Bank mosque was likely result of an electrical fault and not the result of arson; Palestinian officials charge that mosque fire was the work of Jewish extremists.
lead_paragraph: The fire at a mosque near Ramallah last month was most likely caused by an electrical fault, the police said.

headline.main: Arson Ruled Out in Fire at West Bank Mosque, Israeli Police Say
headline.print_headline: West Bank: Arson Is Ruled Out in a Fire at a Mosque, Police Say
